headline: Why Intel Stock Sank Today
summary: Intel stock fell Wednesday as investors reacted to competitive threats.  Rumored leaks suggest that new chips from Nvidia could rival the performance of CPUs from Intel.  Another report suggests that AMD is continuing to win market share from Intel in the server CPU market.

headline: AMD Q2 earnings estimate cut below consensus at KeyBanc
summary: KeyBanc reduced the firm’s Q2 gross margin estimate for AMD (AMD) from 54% to 43% to reflect $800M in charges associated with the write-off of MI308. The firm cut its earnings per share estimate to 47c from 90c, below the consensus of 57c. KeyBanc’s prior estimate excluded the charges given they are one-time in nature. The firm says the majority of consensus estimates now include these charges. It keeps a Sector Weight rating on AMD. Published first on TheFly – the ultimate source for real-time,
